Package: pksensi
Type: Package
Title: Sensitivity analysis for pharmacokinetic model
Version: 0.1.0
Author: Nan-Hung Hsieh, Brad Reisfeld, Frederic Y. Bois, Weihsueh A. Chiu
Maintainer: Nan-Hung Hsieh <nhsieh@cvm.tamu.edu>
Depends: R (>= 3.0.0)
Imports:
    deSolve,
    reshape,
    ggplot2,
    dplyr,
    magrittr
Description: pksensi implements the global sensitivity analysis workflow to investigate the parameter uncertainty and sensitivity in pharmacokinetic (PK) models, especially the physiologically based pharmacokinetic (PBPK) model and advanced compartment absorption and transit (ACAT) model with multivariate output. The package also provide some functions to check the convergence and sensitivity of model parameters.   
License: GPL (>= 3)
RoxygenNote: 6.0.1
Suggests:
    testthat,
    viridis,
    rmarkdown,
    covr,
    knitr
VignetteBuilder: knitr
